review_blob: Nice and hoppy! Smooth and well balanced IPA that I keep stocked in the fridge at all times possible.
Perfect blend of hops and malt. Very well rounded and you can get it in a can.
beer_name: Texas Ale Project Fire Ant Funeral

review_blob: Golden with the mouth feel of a stout. Belgian undertones, but the vanilla comes through immediately for an intense flavor and a satin finish.
My favorite one at this brewery. One of the best porters in Texas. Chocolate and decadent, but not too heavy.
Citrusy and delicious, double IPAs arent my favorite, but this one was definitely great.
beer_name: Texas Ale Project 100 Million Angels Singing
